      "identifier": "ea:concept:internet-culture",
      "name": "Internet Culture",
      "abstract": "Internet culture connects network protocols, web publishing, platform communities, memes, archives, open source, digital folklore and public knowledge systems.",
      "description": "Internet culture is the set of social forms, aesthetics, protocols, communities, memes, archives and practices that emerge through networked communication.",
